Kenyan Port Operations Slow Amid Labor Union Dispute, Business Daily Says

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-09-15T04:42:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/kenyan-port-operations-slow-amid-labor-union-dispute-business-daily-says.html
A record 31 ships are waiting for
clearance at the Kenyan port of  Mombasa  amid a dispute over the
use of private loaders at the facility, Business Daily reported.  The Dock Workers Union wants the Kenya Ports Authority to
halt the use of private workers to move containers at the port,
the Nairobi-based newspaper said, citing Juma Tellah, chief
executive officer of the Kenya Ships Agent Association.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  